name: Bristles - Banksia
description:
The banksia is one of Australia's iconic flowers, growing on trees that can reach heights of 30m in some varieties. When they flower the banksia's large, colourful, and nectar-heavy blooms attract multitudes of insects and birds. The banksia is one of many species if Australian plant that use the heat and smoke from bushfires to trigger the release of seeds from their casings.

Original photography filtered through the lens of generative abstraction. Digital oil painted onto a noisy geometric canvas. 6000x6000. Made in Processing.
